    "attributes": {
        "action": "Ban smartphones for under-18s, starting with 11-12 year olds",
        "additional_details": "Smartphone usage can leads to social media addiction. This has been proven to significantly harm the mental health of young people.\r\n\r\nSmartphone usage is linked to other harms: Exposure to violent imagery; Pornography; Extremist material; Underage gambling; Online bullying and harassment; Harmful Sexual Behaviour; Harmful content such as self-harm and suicide advice.\r\n\r\nWe believe this new law would be welcomed by the vast majority of parents and help protect children.\r\n",
        "background": "Ban smartphones for under-18s; start with current 11-12 year olds and continue for 5 years until illegal for all under-18s. A variety of mobile phones that cannot connect to the internet are available, containing a lot of functionality without the harms that internet connectivity can bring.",
